65. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD892F0E8831470F8D5" authority="(Linnaeus 1753: 377) Link (1831: 140)" authorityName="Link" authorityPageNumber="140" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="377" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[178,845,1781,1809]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892F0E88316B6F8D5" bold="true" box="[178,395,1781,1808]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Senna occidentalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD893D8E8831546F8D5" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[410,635,1782,1809]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref21853" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum, Vol. 2. Imprensis Laurentii Salvii, Stockholm, Sweden, pp. 561 - 1200." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus 1753: 377</bibRefCitation>
) Link (1831: 140)
</taxonomicName>
. (
<figureCitation id="13492A74FF9DFFD89122E88314D3F8D5" box="[864,1006,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="23.[136,229,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-18@23.[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 8. A and B: Senegalia polyphylla: A. branch with inflorescence; B. nectary; C: Senegalia tucumanensis, inflorescence; D: Senegalia velutina, inflorescence; E and F: Senna macranthera: E: branch with inflorescence; F: flower; G and H: Senna obtusifolia: G: branch with inflorescence; H: flower; I and J: Senna occidentalis: I: branch with inflorescence; J: flower; K and L: Sesbania virgata: K. flowers; L: branch with fruit. (A–J; L Rauber CR 2018; K Wink, JG 2019)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424842/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Fig. 8I and J</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368657AFF9DFFDF92CAE9421608FEC5" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892CAE942149CF8B3" blockId="27.[136,1452,1847,2090]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892CAE9421619F894" bold="true" box="[136,292,1847,1873]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Distribution:</emphasis>
It occurs from 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD89392E942151BF894" box="[464,550,1847,1873]" name="Mexico" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD89005E942158BF894" box="[583,694,1847,1873]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD89087E94214F4F894" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[709,969,1847,1873]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" pagination="1 - 918" refId="ref21480" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae - Tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 918." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby 1982</bibRefCitation>
); in 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD891BBE9421300F894" box="[1017,1085,1847,1873]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it occurs throughout the country (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD892D2E92E1640F8B0" author="Flora do Brasil" box="[144,381,1883,1909]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref20723" refString="Flora do Brasil (2020) under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed 10 August 2019)" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD892B4E92E1604F8B0" box="[246,313,1883,1909]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In ParNa Iguaçu it occurs in the Céu Azul area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFE90A1408F878" blockId="27.[136,1452,1847,2090]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFE90A1689F85C" bold="true" box="[189,436,1919,1945]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Reproductive period</emphasis>
: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD8901FE90A1434F85C" author="Queiroz, L. P." box="[605,777,1919,1945]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref22748" refString="Queiroz, L. P. (2009) Leguminosas da Caatinga. Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana / Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew / Associacao Plantas do Nordeste, Feira de Santana." type="book" year="2009">Queiroz (2009)</bibRefCitation>
it flowers and fruits the whole year. In ParNa Iguaçu it was found in flower in January and February, in fruit in February.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFE9B2158AF7EF" blockId="27.[136,1452,1847,2090]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFE9B216C7F824" bold="true" box="[189,506,1991,2017]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Diagnostic characteristics:</emphasis>
Species with pinnate leaves commonly confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD89621E9BD13C5F824" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1123,1272,1991,2018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD89621E9BD13C5F824" box="[1123,1272,1991,2018]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. obtusifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however it can be differentiated by the 2–3 pairs of obovate leaflets with a rounded apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD891B1E99913B5F7C0" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1011,1160,2027,2054]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD891B1E99913B5F7C0" box="[1011,1160,2027,2054]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. obtusifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 4–6 pairs of elliptical leaflets with an acuminate apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD8904FE665158DF7EC" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[525,688,2063,2090]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD8904FE665158DF7EC" box="[525,688,2063,2090]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9AFFDF92FFEEEB16D2FF7D" blockId="28.[136,1451,158,256]" box="[189,495,158,184]" pageId="28" pageNumber="273">
